  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Warehouse Admin Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Receive goods, track deliveries, and liaise with suppliers and supply chain team.</li><li>Provide support to the admin and accounts .</li><li>Assist in printing out orders for packers.</li><li>Prepare delivery orders and arrange job deliveries.</li><li>Compile the vendor invoices & accurately match it against corresponding delivery orders (DO) & purchase orders (PO).</li><li>Generate sales invoice and key in vendor invoices into the system. • Prepare and assist in monthly stock takes.</li><li>General administrative duties but not limited to data entry, filing only.</li><li>Check and verifies all goods/merchandises are received in good condition and quality, also ensuring that the quantity of goods/merchandises received are in accordance with PO, match unit price vs the specification accordance against the PO.</li><li>Ensure that all goods/merchandises received or rejected goods/merchandises are properly documented and accounted for.</li><li>Account for any discrepancies in the physical inventories and advise in-charge of any material differences.</li><li>Implement proper control in maintain security of all storage area</li><li>Follow up on any outstanding orders for goods  that have not been received and follow the protocols of reporting outstanding orders</li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned by direct supervisor.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Candidate must possess at least a GCE \"O' Level or Diploma in logistics or supply chain management.</li><li>Preferably at least 3 years of work experience in warehouse .</li><li>Working knowledge of ERP software like Navision or SAP is an advantage.</li><li>Possess initiative to understand work flows and processes in order to work efficiently and effectively.</li><li>Ability to work as a group and individual with effective organizational and follow-up skills.</li><li>Good interpersonal skills and able to interact with all levels, internally and externally in a professional and responsive manner.</li></ul>",
